# Part 2

## Describe a plan that you had to change recently.

Recently, I had to change one of my study plans for the IELTS exam. This happened about a month ago when I realized that my original schedule was far too ambitious and honestly a bit unrealistic.

At first, I planned to spend almost all my free time practicing reading and listening because I believed those two sections could improve quickly with intensive practice. I even made a strict timetable for myself, studying more than six hours a day after classes. However, after following that routine for around two weeks, I started to feel mentally exhausted. More importantly, I noticed that my speaking and writing skills weren’t improving as much as I expected because I had been neglecting them.

So I decided to completely adjust my plan. Instead of focusing only on input-based skills like reading and listening, I created a more balanced schedule. I began practicing speaking every day by recording my answers and using AI tools to correct my pronunciation and grammar. I also started writing at least one Task 2 essay every two days and reviewing advanced vocabulary systematically.

At first, I felt a little frustrated because changing the plan made me feel as if I had wasted time. But later, I realized that being flexible is actually very important. A perfect plan on paper doesn’t always work in real life. After changing my strategy, I became much more productive and less stressed, and I also felt more confident about my exam preparation.

So overall, although changing the plan was slightly stressful in the beginning, it turned out to be a very positive decision.

---

## 中文翻译

最近，我不得不改变自己的一个雅思备考计划。这件事大概发生在一个月前，当时我意识到原来的学习安排太理想化了，说实话有点不现实。

一开始，我计划把几乎所有空闲时间都花在阅读和听力上，因为我认为这两个部分通过大量练习可以提升得很快。我甚至给自己制定了一个非常严格的时间表，每天下课后学习六个多小时。然而，在坚持了大约两周之后，我开始感到精神疲惫。更重要的是，我发现自己的口语和写作并没有像预期那样提高，因为我忽略了它们。

于是我决定彻底调整计划。我不再只专注于输入型技能，比如阅读和听力，而是制定了一个更加平衡的学习安排。我开始每天练习口语，通过录音和 AI 工具纠正自己的发音和语法。我还开始每两天写一篇 Task 2 作文，并系统地复习高级词汇。

刚开始时，我其实有点沮丧，因为改变计划让我觉得之前浪费了时间。但后来我意识到，保持灵活其实非常重要。纸面上的完美计划，在现实中不一定有效。调整策略之后，我的学习效率更高了，压力也更小了，而且我对考试更有信心了。

所以总体来说，虽然一开始改变计划让我有点焦虑，但结果证明这是一个非常正确的决定。

